main event: A 13-year-old witness observed an unidentified flying object over Round Lake, Illinois on December 7, 1969.
interesting points: The object was described as round and silver in color, appearing to have a rim around the outer edge.
The object moved at a high rate of speed and passed over the witness's car at an altitude of approximately 200 feet before disappearing.
The object made no sound as it passed overhead.
The witness provided a sketch depicting the shape and trajectory of the object.
The report includes details about the time, location, duration of the sighting, and the witness's observations.
sighted object: a round, silver object with a rim
